						               													<description>A new Corps/Army level WWII East Front game:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The map is about 30&amp;quot; x 44&amp;quot; or, the same size as &amp;quot;Deluxe Bitter Woods&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is a ONE PIECE map, harder board, just like the maps used in The Russian Campaign 4th ed. and Deluxe Bitter Woods.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The complexity is more advanced than both games but the concepts are similar. If you know TRC, you will grasp RB easily.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In fact, if you love TRC, this is your next logical progression forward to a more robust game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The things to get used to are:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; unit breakdowns&amp;#10;&amp;bull; building units up based on steps&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Stukas fly from airports (cities/towns), not HQ's&amp;#10;&amp;bull; HQ's hold and release reserves&amp;#10;&amp;bull; it costs 1 movement point to cross rivers&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Leader counters can impact the die&amp;#10;&amp;bull; d10 Combat Results Table with step loses&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Blitzkreig Combat Results table that sacrifices unit kills for penetration through the enemy line, armor can advance moving through ZOCs to create encirclements&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Stukas fly in both impulses but maximums are placed on how many can fly in the second impulse based on weather&amp;#10;&amp;bull; larger, more historical Order of Battle&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Partisans come in two stages, the deadlier form can be built if the simple form is left on the board unmolested&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Lend-Lease is much more accurate and is split into 3 historical entry points&amp;#10;&amp;bull; NEW impulse rail movement&amp;#10;&amp;bull; NEW revised weather table&amp;#10;&amp;bull; NEW revised Play Aid Chart&amp;#10;&amp;bull; NEW open turn speial rules&amp;#10;&amp;bull; NEW optional rules and enhanced standard rules&amp;#10;&amp;bull; and much more&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
